# Smart Presence System - Technical Diagrams

This document contains the complete architectural and structural diagrams for the Smart Presence application. 
The system is designed as a **Local-First, Offline-Ready Architecture** with an **Optional Intelligent Automation Layer**.

---

## 1. System Architecture (High-Level)
> [!NOTE]
> The **Core Bridge** (Browser -> Frontend -> Backend -> DB) is the essential path. 
> The **Intelligent Layer** (LLM -> MCP) is a "hollow" add-on feature for autonomous operations.

```mermaid
graph TB
    %% Core Infrastructure Styling
    classDef core fill:#f9f9f9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef database fill:#e1f5fe,stroke:#01579b,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef intelligent fill:#ffffff,stroke:#999,stroke-width:2px,stroke-dasharray: 5 5;

    subgraph Client["Client Interface"]
        Browser["🌐 Web Browser\n(Standard UI)"]:::core
        AI_LLM["🧠 AI Assistant / LLM\n(User's LLM)"]:::intelligent
    end

    subgraph CoreApp["CORE APPLICATION (Offline Loop)"]
        direction TB
        Frontend["⚛️ React Frontend\n(Vite @ :3000)"]:::core
        Backend["🚀 FastAPI Backend\n(Uvicorn @ :8000)"]:::core
        
        subgraph Engine["Local ML Engine"]
            InsightFace["InsightFace (CPU)"]:::core
            ONNX["ONNX Runtime"]:::core
        end
    end

    subgraph AddonLayer["INTELLIGENT AUTOMATION (Add-on Feature)"]
        direction TB
        MCP["🔌 MCP Server\n(JSON-RPC Gateway)"]:::intelligent
    end

    subgraph DataLayer["LOCAL DATA (Persistence)"]
        direction LR
        SQLite[("📂 SQLite DB\n(Relational)")]:::database
        ChromaDB[("🧬 ChromaDB\n(Vector Store)")]:::database
    end

    %% Core Path
    Browser -->|HTTPS| Frontend
    Frontend -->|REST API| Backend
    Backend -->|SQL| SQLite
    Backend -->|Embeddings| InsightFace
    InsightFace -->|Vectors| ChromaDB

    %% Add-on Path (Hollowed)
    AI_LLM -.->|stdio / RPC| MCP
    MCP -.->|Internal API calls| Backend

    linkStyle 5,6 stroke:#999,stroke-width:1px,stroke-dasharray: 3;
```

